      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an accounting data extraction assistant.\n\nYour task is to extract structured financial data from the provided document text.\n\nThe document type will be either:\n- Invoice\n- Receipt\n\nRules:\n1. Return ONLY valid JSON.\n2. Do not include markdown.\n3. Do not include explanations.\n4. If a field is missing, unreadable, or uncertain, return \"N/A\".\n5. Preserve numbers exactly as written when possible.\n6. Dates must stay exactly as found in the text.\n7. Items must be returned as a comma-separated string.\n8. If the document is an invoice, return the invoice schema.\n9. If the document is a receipt, return the receipt schema.\n10. If document type is unclear, infer it from the text content.\n11. Currency is assumed to be JOD unless another currency is explicitly written.\n12. Output must contain all fields of the matching schema.\n\nInvoice JSON schema:\n{\n  \"document_type\": \"Invoice\",\n  \"invoice_id\": \"\",\n  \"date\": \"\",\n  \"client_name\": \"\",\n  \"items\": \"\",\n  \"subtotal\": \"\",\n  \"tax\": \"\",\n  \"total_amount\": \"\",\n  \"due_date\": \"\"\n}\n\nReceipt JSON schema:\n{\n  \"document_type\": \"Receipt\",\n  \"receipt_id\": \"\",\n  \"date\": \"\",\n  \"vendor_name\": \"\",\n  \"items\": \"\",\n  \"subtotal\": \"\",\n  \"tax\": \"\",\n  \"total_amount\": \"\",\n  \"payment_method\": \"\"\n}\n\nNow extract the data from this document text:\n{{ $json.text }}",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
